# Safety And No Fake Code

## Non-Negotiables

- Do not write fake code.
- Do not claim success unless the result is real.
- Do not use placeholder-only implementations unless they are clearly marked as `TODO`.
- Do not add hardcoded secrets, API keys, tokens, or credentials.
- Do not introduce paid APIs or backend assumptions by default.
- Do not add hidden network behavior.

## Safety Rules

- Keep Nova / Luna separate from Jarvis and unrelated workflows.
- Preserve user control over automation.
- Respect platform security boundaries.
- Do not bypass device protections or security gates.
- Keep the assistant local-first and on-device as much as possible.

## Verification Rules

- Add or update tests when behavior changes.
- Validate changes before reporting them as done.
- If a command, test, or build was not run, say so clearly.
- Keep the project honest about what is implemented, partial, or planned.

## Change Discipline

- Avoid unrelated edits.
- Preserve useful existing content.
- Keep docs and reports aligned with actual behavior.
- Use clean, practical implementations instead of fake success messages.
